body:
The reason current behavior exists is to not have data loss. But then when I look at the code, it seems that the transform logic can throw exceptions and we do not stop consuming. I see no reason why decoder can also be put into the [try/catch](https://github.com/apache/pinot/blob/master/pinot-core/src/main/java/org/apache/pinot/core/data/manager/realtime/LLRealtimeSegmentDataManager.java#L524).

This way, consumption will not stop unless underlying stream has a problem.

@sajjad-moradi ?

@saurabhd336 I cannot add comments to your design doc. Also, please close this PR and add your design doc to the issue (create one if there is none). 

Thanks

If you are not modifying zk this may be simple enough that you don't need a design doc, but since you already have one, that is fine.
